From 445aa5bfae378f96f6ea851a232b18d9328a6945 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Jul 2025 09:39:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: add support for dynamic link
 addition and removal in AP MLD

Extend ath12k's change_sta_links() to support multi-link reconfiguration
for associated stations in AP MLD, as defined in IEEE 802.11be
(D7.0, section 35.3.6.4).

When a reconfiguration request is received from a non-AP MLD,
mac80211 invokes drv_change_sta_links() with reconf.added_links and/or
reconf.removed_links populated to perform reconfiguration at ath12k driver.

Handle  ML reconfig using a new ath12k_sta_ml_reconfig_handler(), which:
- Sends peer association commands for all valid links.
- Installs pairwise keys and authorizes newly added links.

Reconfiguration handling is triggered only when reconf flags are set,
preserving existing behavior for regular link updates. These flags are set
exclusively by mac80211 to distinguish MLO reconfiguration from regular
link changes.

Signed-off-by: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
